#: ../../source/scale/high-availability-cluster-based-deployment.rst:611
msgid "Red server status"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scale/high-availability-cluster-based-deployment.rst:613
msgid ""
"When high availability mode is enabled, the System Console displays the "
"server status as red or green, indicating if the servers are "
"communicating correctly with the cluster. The servers use inter-node "
"communication to ping the other machines in the cluster, and once a ping "
"is established the servers exchange information, such as server version "
"and configuration files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scale/high-availability-cluster-based-deployment.rst:615
msgid "A server status of red can occur for the following reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scale/high-availability-cluster-based-deployment.rst:617
msgid ""
"**Configuration file mismatch:** Mattermost will still attempt the inter-"
"node communication, but the System Console will show a red status for the"
" server since the high availability mode feature assumes the same "
"configuration file to function properly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scale/high-availability-cluster-based-deployment.rst:618
msgid ""
"**Server version mismatch:** Mattermost will still attempt the inter-node"
" communication, but the System Console will show a red status for the "
"server since the high availability mode feature assumes the same version "
"of Mattermost is installed on each server in the cluster. It is "
"recommended to use the `latest version of Mattermost "
"<https://mattermost.com/download/>`__ on all servers. Follow the upgrade "
"procedure in :doc:`../upgrade/upgrading-mattermost-server` for any server"
" that needs to be upgraded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scale/high-availability-cluster-based-deployment.rst:619
msgid ""
"**Server is down:** If an inter-node communication fails to send a "
"message it makes another attempt in 15 seconds. If the second attempt "
"fails, the server is assumed to be down. An error message is written to "
"the logs and the System Console shows a status of red for that server. "
"The inter-node communication continues to ping the down server in 15 "
"second intervals. When the server comes back up, any new messages are "
"sent to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scale/high-availability-cluster-based-deployment.rst:622
msgid "WebSocket disconnect"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scale/high-availability-cluster-based-deployment.rst:624
msgid ""
"When a client WebSocket receives a disconnect it will automatically "
"attempt to re-establish a connection every three seconds with a backoff. "
"After the connection is established, the client attempts to receive any "
"messages that were sent while it was disconnected."
msgstr ""

